## The two failure categories

```text
Retriable failures (transient):
  - DB temporarily unavailable → retry after 1-2s will succeed
  - External HTTP timeout → retry after 5s will succeed
  - Network blip → retry immediately

Non-retriable failures (permanent):
  - Malformed JSON → retrying 1000 times won't fix it
  - Unknown enum value → code change needed
  - Business rule violation → data must be fixed manually

Poison pill: a message that will ALWAYS fail → blocks the entire partition
  Consumer keeps retrying it → all subsequent messages in partition are stuck
```

---

## Step 1: Configure DefaultErrorHandler with ExponentialBackOff

```java
@Configuration
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class KafkaConsumerConfig {

    private final KafkaTemplate<String, Object> kafkaTemplate;

    @Bean
    public DefaultErrorHandler kafkaErrorHandler() {

        // Where to send failed messages after all retries exhausted
        DeadLetterPublishingRecoverer recoverer = new DeadLetterPublishingRecoverer(
            kafkaTemplate,
            // DLT topic name = original topic + ".DLT"
            (record, ex) -> {
                log.error("Sending to DLT: topic={}, partition={}, offset={}, error={}",
                    record.topic(), record.partition(), record.offset(), ex.getMessage());
                return new TopicPartition(
                    record.topic() + ".DLT",
                    // Use same partition as original (preserves ordering context)
                    record.partition());
            }
        );

        // Retry: 1s → 2s → 4s (3 attempts)
        ExponentialBackOff backoff = new ExponentialBackOff(1000L, 2.0);
        backoff.setMaxAttempts(3);
        backoff.setMaxInterval(10000L);  // cap at 10s between retries

        DefaultErrorHandler handler = new DefaultErrorHandler(recoverer, backoff);

        // NON-RETRIABLE: send directly to DLT without retrying
        handler.addNotRetryableExceptions(
            JsonParseException.class,         // malformed JSON
            DeserializationException.class,   // can't deserialize
            ConstraintViolationException.class // business rule violation
        );

        // Add listener for observability
        handler.setRetryListeners(new RetryListener() {
            @Override
            public void failedDelivery(ConsumerRecord<?, ?> record,
                    Exception ex, int deliveryAttempt) {
                log.warn("Retry attempt {} for topic={} partition={} offset={}: {}",
                    deliveryAttempt, record.topic(), record.partition(),
                    record.offset(), ex.getMessage());
                retryCounter.increment(deliveryAttempt);  // Prometheus metric
            }

            @Override
            public void recovered(ConsumerRecord<?, ?> record, Exception ex) {
                log.info("Message RECOVERED (sent to DLT) topic={} offset={}",
                    record.topic(), record.offset());
                dlqCounter.increment();
            }

            @Override
            public void recoveryFailed(ConsumerRecord<?, ?> record,
                    Exception original, Exception failure) {
                log.error("Failed to send to DLT! original={} dlqError={}",
                    original.getMessage(), failure.getMessage());
                alertingService.sendCriticalAlert("DLT send failed", record);
            }
        });

        return handler;
    }

    @Bean
    public ConcurrentKafkaListenerContainerFactory<String, Object>
            kafkaListenerContainerFactory(
                ConsumerFactory<String, Object> consumerFactory,
                DefaultErrorHandler errorHandler) {

        var factory = new ConcurrentKafkaListenerContainerFactory<String, Object>();
        factory.setConsumerFactory(consumerFactory);
        factory.setCommonErrorHandler(errorHandler);
        return factory;
    }
}
```

