## Your interview answer

> "I configured DefaultErrorHandler with two key features: ExponentialBackOff (1s, 2s, 4s — 3 attempts) for retriable failures like temporary DB outages, and a NotRetryable list for permanent failures like JsonParseException that will never succeed regardless of retries. After all retries, messages go to a .DLT topic. A DLT consumer reads them, adds context headers (original offset, exception class, message), and saves to a database table. Engineering gets a Slack alert for non-retriable errors. After fixing the root cause, engineers replay via REST API. This eliminates partition blocking — bad messages are moved to DLT immediately, and subsequent messages continue processing."

