**Problem**: Message originally processed PARTIALLY before failing (e.g., DB write succeeded but email send failed → message in DLT). Replaying it causes the DB write to run again → duplicate order.

**Fix: Idempotency key in every consumer**

```java
@KafkaListener(topics = "order.events")
@Transactional
public void consume(String payload, @Header(KafkaHeaders.OFFSET) long offset,
        @Header(KafkaHeaders.RECEIVED_TOPIC) String topic) {

    OrderEvent event = objectMapper.readValue(payload, OrderEvent.class);

    // Idempotency check using event's own ID
    String idempotencyKey = event.getEventId().toString();
    if (processedEventRepo.existsByEventId(idempotencyKey)) {
        log.info("Duplicate event {} skipped (already processed)", idempotencyKey);
        return;  // safe to ack — already done
    }

    // Process
    orderService.processOrder(event);
    emailService.sendConfirmation(event);

    // Mark as processed — in same transaction as orderService
    processedEventRepo.save(new ProcessedEvent(idempotencyKey, Instant.now()));
    // If DB commits → both order and processed-event saved
    // If email fails → DB rolls back → event retried → idempotency check stops duplicate order
}
```

**For DLQ replay specifically:**
```java
@PostMapping("/dlq/replay/{id}")
public void replay(@PathVariable Long id) {
    DlqMessage msg = dlqRepo.findById(id).orElseThrow();
    if (msg.getStatus() == DlqStatus.REPLAYED) {
        throw new IllegalStateException("Already replayed — idempotency protection");
    }
    // The consumer's own idempotency check will handle duplication
    kafka.send(msg.getOriginalTopic(), msg.getPayload());
    msg.setStatus(DlqStatus.REPLAYED);
    dlqRepo.save(msg);
}
```

